# Terminal Behavior Rules
- When running terminal commands on Arch Linux, always ensure the process self-terminates.
- If a command finishes quickly, the PTY buffer might hang. 
- ALWAYS wrap execution in this pattern to force an I/O flush:
  ( [command] ) && echo "FINISH" > /dev/$(tty) && exit

# Git Rules
- Never run `git commit` without the user explicitly asking to commit.

